    About Commercial Lighting

    When it comes to lighting up your office, garage workshops or other work spaces, choosing the best commercial lighting is important. Whether youre looking for LED grow lights, LED panel lights, emergency lights, work lights, commercial light fixtures or fluorescent light fixtures, we have lots of great commercial lighting options for you to choose from.

    Choosing LED Lighting

    LED stands for light-emitting diode, the technology behind LED lighting. LEDs emit almost no heat or UV rays. LED lighting comes in many shapes, sizes, colors and temperatures.

    LED shop lights embody the traditional look of a garage, a single bar of light fixture, usually hanging by a chain assembly, although they can be ceiling-mounted as well. Most of these easy-to-install shop lights just plug in to an outlet. Whether you choose LED shop lights or the traditional fluorescent type, they are a quick, affordable way to get your garage work area nice and bright. Some LED shop lights are designed to be hard-wired; these are more expensive, but the integrated lighting allows you to add accessories such as a motion sensor.

    LED strip lights are easy to install and come in several sizes to allow you to fully customize your overhead garage lighting or work spaces. LED strip light fixtures of this type supply instant light with no warmup period, but if you have fluorescent fixtures of this type, you can upgrade to LED with a retrofit kit. This is more affordable than replacing a large number of strip light fixtures.

    Consider LED high bay lights when selecting lighting for very high ceilings. LED high bay lights with a wide distribution pattern are best to reduce the number of overall fixtures youll have to install. Youll need to choose bulbs that can maintain a high output of lumens. We also have lots of LED light fixtures for your lighting needs.

    Additional Commercial Lighting Options

    Producing your own fresh, homegrown food year-round isnt that far away with our grow lights. Lack of water, light and even outdoor space often prohibits year-round gardening for many people. Growing indoors with proper lighting is your answer.

    Other commercial lights include LED work lights and troffer lights. We even have a large selection of exit signs.  

    Let Us Help You

    If you need assistance completing your commercial lighting project, were here to help. Be sure to check out our Types of LED Lights guide, or our How to Choose the Best Lighting for Your Garage Workshop guide.
